The condition of a living being when its life has been suspended but not terminated -- usually as the result of rapid, cryogenic freezing.  

This has been proposed in '''science fiction''' stories as a means of allowing human beings to withstand inter-stellar journies lasting hundreds of years without aging; their bodies being revived to full functionality upon arrival at the destination.

Reportedly, some wealthy people with terminal illnesses pay to have their bodies quick-frozen and maintained indefinitely so they can be revived when a cure for their illness has been developed.